## 🧑🏾‍🏫 what this challenge teaches u
the more u avoid manual url encoding in javascript, the less mental issues u will have in future
the trick here is to use encodeURIComponent for the payload
since some chars r not encoded as we think, for example + - = & ... the best option is to save the normal string into a constant and then encode it with encodeURIComponent
in the second level javascript (reflected-xss in /ephemeral endpoint) u can use fetch or window.location
best option is fetch because it is silent and not visible avoiding visible page redirection as window.location does
u can use fetch also because SOP and SameSite r not a problem:
-SOP -> the goal is just sending the request, not to read the response
-SameSite -> u r not sending any cookie in the headers, u r exfiltrating cookie value from document.cookie and put it in the URL as query string

